==English==

===Etymology===
Latin ''[[prodigus]]'', "profuse", "extravagant", from ''[[prodigere]]'', "to drive forth", "to squander away", from ''[[pro#Latin|pro]]'', "forward", "forth", + ''[[agere]]'', "to drive". Confer French ''prodigue''.

===Adjective===
'''prodigal'''
#[[rash]]ly or [[wasteful]]ly [[extravagant]]; as, prodigal expenditures on unneeded weaponry, a prodigal life
#giving or given in [[abundance]]; [[lavish]] or [[profuse]]; as, prodigal praise

===Noun===
'''prodigal'''
#one who is given to [[wasteful]] [[luxury]] or [[extravagance]]

